{# Compact memory-context template (v12 M7 Task 7.6).

Renders retrieved memory entries inline, comma-separated, with no
headers. Useful when the total context budget is tight and bullet-list
overhead is unwelcome.

Inputs match `default.j2` — the two templates are interchangeable at
wire-time via `MemoryConfig.context_template`.
#}
{% set count = entry_count | default(entries | length) %}
{% if count > 0 %}
Memory: {% for entry in entries %}{{ (entry.text[:(max_entry_chars | default(120))]) | e }}{% if entry.text | length > (max_entry_chars | default(120)) %}…{% endif %}{% if not loop.last %}; {% endif %}{% endfor %}

{% endif %}
